   - "What would make you stick with a new tool after 30 days?"\
\
4. Pricing & commitment (3 min)\
   - "If NoxReach helped you book 1 extra gig per year, what would that be worth to you?"\
   - "At what monthly price would this feel like a no-brainer? Too expensive to consider?"\
\
5. Close (optional)\
   - "Can I follow up with you in 2 weeks to see if your workflow changed?"\
```\
\
#### Promoter Interview Script (20 min)\
```\
1. Warm-up (2 min)\
   - "How do you typically discover new DJs for your events?"\
   - "What does a 'good' DJ inquiry look like to you?"\
\
2. Decision process (10 min)\
   - "Walk me through how you evaluate an incoming DJ inquiry. What do you look for first?"\
   - "What makes you reply vs. archive vs. defer?"\
   - "What format do you prefer for receiving DJ materials (EPK, links, attachments)?"\
\
3. Friction points (5 min)\
   - "What's the most frustrating part of managing DJ inquiries?"\
   - "Have you ever worked with a DJ who used a 'booking system'? Did it help or hinder?"\
\
4. Opportunity validation (3 min)\
   - "If a tool could help DJs send you better-organized, promoter-friendly inquiries, would you prefer that?"\
   - "What one change would make your life easier when evaluating DJs?"\
\
5. Close\
   - "Would you be open to testing a promoter-friendly inquiry template we're designing?"\
```\
\
### 3.3 The One Thing to Fix This Week\
\
**Stop optimizing the landing page in isolation**.\
\
Your page is good enough to convert *if* the underlying product-market fit assumptions are correct. But if you haven't validated:\
- That promoters respond to structured outreach\
- That DJs will stick around after the novelty wears off\
- That \'8019/month feels like a bargain against lost gigs\
\
...then you're polishing a funnel that leads to a leaky bucket.\
\
**Do this now**:  \
Pick *one* of the research angles above (start with #1: promoter behavior) and run 3 interviews this week. The insights will change your messaging, your roadmap, and your pricing more than any copy tweak.\
\
> **Brutal truth**: Great landing pages convert visitors. Great *research* converts skeptics into believers. You have the first. Go earn the second.\
